Reasoning: The paper discusses issues related to the implementation of asynchronous logic circuits, which falls under the category of Electronic Design Automation (EDA) and Computer-Aided Design (CAD) in computer science. Specifically, the paper focuses on delay-insensitive, robust asynchronous logic, multi-level decomposition, and physical implementation, which are relevant to the sub-categories of Emerging Technologies (cs.ET), Architecture (cs.AR), Digital Circuits (cs.DC), Electromagnetics (cs.EM), and Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO).
